The paper deals with interference modeling in mobile cellular systems, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper proposes a new model for characterizing aggregate interference statistics, which involves the manipulation and analysis of data. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category, which deals with the design, implementation, and evaluation of computer networks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of stochastic geometry, which is a mathematical framework for modeling spatial phenomena, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also mentions the prediction of signal-to-interference-ratio- and rate statistics, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category, which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. Finally, the paper mentions the application of base station coordination- and cooperation schemes, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category, which deals with the application of game theory to computer science problems.
